  "details": "A Library providing simplified C and Python API to libsolv.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in libdnf&apos;s signature verification functionality in versions before 0.60.1. This flaw allows an attacker to achieve code execution if they can alter the header information of an RPM package and then trick a user or system into installing it. The highest risk of this vulnerability is to confidentiality, integrity, as well as system availability.(CVE-2021-3445)",
